# Fieldnotes — Code Review
#
# Run after writing Ruby, ERB, or CSS code.
# Focus: quality, duplication, simplicity for solo long-term maintenance.

---

## Code Quality & Simplicity

- [ ] Can I understand this code in 6 months without context?
- [ ] Methods under 15 lines, classes under 100 — split if larger
- [ ] No dead code, no commented-out blocks, no TODO without a plan
- [ ] Single responsibility — each method does one thing, each class has one reason to change
- [ ] Naming says what it does — no abbreviations, no generic `data`/`result`/`item`
- [ ] No premature abstractions — three similar lines are better than a clever helper used once

---

## Duplication

- [ ] Is this logic already implemented elsewhere? Search before writing
- [ ] Shared across 2+ places → extract to concern, service, or ViewComponent
- [ ] Used once → leave inline, do not extract
- [ ] Same query in multiple controllers → move to model scope
- [ ] Same HTML pattern in multiple views → ViewComponent (not partial) if it has logic

---

## Rails Conventions

- [ ] Rails 8 built-in over gem (Solid Queue, rate_limit, fresh_when, built-in auth)
- [ ] `includes()` on collections — no N+1
- [ ] `fresh_when @record` on public show/index
- [ ] Public controllers fire `Rails.event.notify` for analytics
- [ ] Admin inherits `Admin::BaseController`
- [ ] Fat model, skinny controller — logic in models/services, not controllers
- [ ] Callbacks only for data integrity, never for side effects (use jobs)

---

## ERB & CSS

- [ ] Design tokens from `tokens.css` — no hardcoded colors/spacing/fonts
- [ ] Stimulus for interactivity — no JS libraries
- [ ] No `.variant()` inline in views — warm via `ImageVariantJob`
- [ ] `<picture>` with AVIF/WebP/JPEG, not plain `image_tag` for photos

---

## Security & Privacy

- [ ] No secrets in code
- [ ] No external requests (CDN, fonts, scripts, trackers)
- [ ] File uploads validated (type, size)
- [ ] No Turbo Stream broadcasts to unauthenticated users
